This software enables to synchronize slides with the corresponding video recording 

http://slideotracker.googlecode.com/files/icon.png

*slideotracker = slides + video + tracking* 

== Screencast == 
<wiki:video url="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=74yZJ63h-Ow" />

== Usage == 
{{{
Usage: slideotracker.py [options]

Options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -v video, --video=video
                        video file name
  -s SLIDESDIR, --slides-dir=SLIDESDIR
                        slides directory ( slide-1.jpg, slide-2.jpg, ...)
  -p PRECISION, --precision=PRECISION
                        precision in number of frame (default 25)
  -o OUTFILE, --out=OUTFILE
                        output file name, by default results.js
  -f FORMAT, --format=FORMAT
                        output file format js (default),csv
  -d, --debug           debug trace

}}} 

Example :
{{{
#extract pdf pages to jpeg using ImageMagick
mkdir /tmp/mypdf/
convert <your.pdf> /tmp/mypdf/slide.jpg
#read with slide filename pattern : slide-(\d+).jpg

python slideotracker.py -v <videopath> -s /tmp/mypdf/ -o results.txt

}}}

Results in Javascript format :
{{{
slides=[0, 1, 2];
frames=[500, 850, 950];
}}} 

Results in CSV format :
{{{
#slide_number;star_frame;end_frame
0;0;500
1;500;850
2;850;950
...
..
.
}}} 


== Dependencies == 

  * Scikit-Learn 
  * OpenCV 2.0

